,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>This page demonstrates calculating a value from all the data in the client side data model.',
'A few people have wanted to process the whole data model on the client. ',
'For example calculating the total of a column and keeping it in sync as the grid is edited. ',
'See <a href=''https://community.oracle.com/thread/4003463'' target=''_blank''>here</a>,',
'<a href=''https://community.oracle.com/thread/4005143'' target=''_blank''>here</a> and',
'<a href=''https://community.oracle.com/message/14174982'' target=''_blank''>here</a>',
'</p>',
'<p>The assumption is that the model is going to contain all the data. There are',
'many uses cases where the amount of data is of a resonable size. Care must be ',
'taken that too much data isn''t loaded on the client.',
'Currently the server sends only 50 records initially (if Lazy Loading is No). ',
'The client fetches more data as needed; currently 100 records at a time by default.',
'The model fetchAll method is used to ensure that the model contains all the data.',
'This code can be removed if you are sure the number of records is always less',
'than 50.',
'</p>',
'<p>Client side calcualations should be advisory only. ',
'The server should validate or redo all calculations. Fields updated should probably have',
'warn on unsaved changes set to ignore or perhaps they are display/read only.',
'There is an extra insert model notification due to auto add row when the report changes. To ',
'avoid this set Add Row If Empty to No.</p>',
'<p>This page demonstrates the correct method of getting access to the model and',
'subscribing to model notifications. Once you get access to the model, looping',
'and doing the calculation is easy. The problem is that the model itself is destroyed',
'and created over time. Also there are many changes that can affect the calculation.',
'That is why a model notification listener is subscribed so that the calculation',
'can be redone when needed. In this example the calculation is only done',
'for the grid model model so a viewchange notification is used to hide the total',
'when the grid view is not the current view. A jQuery selector is used rather than a region',
'because specifying an IG region changes the definition of Fire on Initialization',
'to be when a row is edited and here we want page load.',
'</p>',
'<p>Demonstrates:<br>',
'Loading all the data (use with caution), Looping over the data to calculate a value.',
'Handling the custom viewchange event.',
'<br>Customizations:<br>',
'See Page attribute JavaScript: Function and Global Variable Declaration.',
'Dynamic Action view change. Play around with pagination settings, view',
'definitions, lazy loading, and saved Reports.',
'<br>Issues:<br>',
'Seems like a viewchange event on the IG region should have Fire on Initialization',
'apply to page load not row edit.',
'</p>',
''))
,p_plug_query_options=>'DERIVED_REPORT_COLUMNS'
,p_attribute_01=>'N'
,p_attribute_02=>'HTML'
);
