,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>This page demonstrates how to change the default height of rows in the grid',
'view as well as having an icon column and putting the extra height to good use',
'for the Notes column. It also shows how to handle extra high column headings.',
'In this case the Employee Name column has an explicit &lt;br> so that it wraps.',
'</p>',
'<p>This was asked in this <a href=''https://community.oracle.com/message/14161862#14161862'' target=''_blank''>thread</a>. ',
'See that thread for info about using blob columns etc. To keep this example',
'simple it is using old images that come with APEX.',
'This example shows how to customize the row height as described ',
'<a href=''http://hardlikesoftware.com/weblog/2017/01/06/interactive-grid-column-widths/'' target=''_blank''>here</a>.',
'A strange thing happens when the grid is also editable some controls that would ',
'be popups are not if they fit in the height but then they may not fit the width.',
'See the textarea Notes field for example. One way to deal with this is to make ',
'the height larger than the row (see width and height attributes). ',
'Another alternative is to use CSS to make it fix exactly (see inline CSS rule ',
'for #C_NOTES and uncomment). A drawback is that when in in navigation ',
'mode it would be nice if the text would wrap to fill available space. ',
'If you use the technique from the above blog using HTML Expression (&lt;div class="wrap-cell">&amp;NOTES.&lt;/div>) ',
'then it cannot be edited. This can be solved by using the advanced column',
'config property cellTemplate.',
'</p>',
'<p>This page also demonstrates a custom icon view using the same image. ',
'The default (non-custom) icon view sets a default height/width but requires a ',
'full URL for the image. The IMAGE column doesn''t have the full URL because it',
'would make the data larger. Custom icon markup is used to get around this. ',
'CSS rules are added to the page to set the height and width style. ',
'This also shows how to set multiple select for icon view.',
'</p>',
'<p>Demonstrates:<br>',
'Customizing IG CSS styles. Advanced configuration to set noStretch on the IMAGE column',
'and cellTemplate on the NOTES column so that it can be edited and still show multiple ',
'lines in navigation mode.',
'<br>Customizations:<br>',
'See Page attribute CSS: Inline. See Source SQL Query for how the IMAGE column is defined ',
'(note that by not defining the full URL it keeps the size of the data smaller).',
'See Column attribute Advanced: JavaScript Code for NOTES and IMAGE. See ',
'custom Icon view definition and Advanced: JavaScript code that enables multiple',
'selection for Icon view.',
'<br>Issues:<br>',
'The Icon view selection and focus styles need improvement; See fixes in CSS: Inline.<br>',
'It should be easier to set multiple selection for icon view.',
'</p>'))
,p_plug_query_options=>'DERIVED_REPORT_COLUMNS'
,p_attribute_01=>'N'
,p_attribute_02=>'HTML'
