,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>Interactive Grid does not support row reordering out of the box.',
'But the grid widget and the model do have some minimal support for reordering.',
'This can be seen in the Columns dialog (remember that all the IG dialogs use a model',
'instance, and recordView widget and optional grid widget). One limitation is',
'that you don''t get much control over how the sequence column is managed. The ',
'sequence column must allow decimal numbers.',
'</p>',
'<p>This is a somewhat typical task list UI with extra columns to warrant using a grid.',
'It can manage multiple task lists.',
'The main difference is no drag and drop because the grid widget doesn''t support that.',
'You can select multiple records and mark them all complete using the selection action menu.',
'Reordering assumes that all the records are on the client so the model fetchAll method is called.',
'For this reason reordering works best with small result sets. Sorting doesn''t',
'make much sense because the order must always be the sequence order. Adding ',
'order by to the SQL isn''t allowed so must make the sequence column (SEQ)',
'visible temporarily then set sort report settings so just that column is sorted ascending.',
'Then the column can be hidden (see issues below). Turn off sorting for all the other columns.',
'Makes most sense to use scroll paging.',
'</p>',
'<p>Demonstrates:<br>',
'Using the model moveRecords API and sequenceField, sequenceStep options to reorder',
'rows.<br>',
'Adding custom actions and adding them to the toolbar and selection action menu.<br>',
'Custom Add Row button.<br>',
'SQL where clause based on page item and refresh IG and update column default when page item changes.<br>',
'How to workaround the no data found error when saving due to records being moved outside the ',
'where clause hard coded in the IG SQL. This can happen when Show Completed = No and you',
'mark a task as completed. (Search for P11_SAVING)<br>',
'How to workaround the columns with a display value showing the value for an inserted row.<br>',
'A button and inline dialog to implement a poor man''s combo box.',
'<br>Customizations:<br>',
'See Advanced JavaScript Code for action definitions and all customizations. See ',
'change list DA for how switching lists works including how the LIST column for ',
'inserted rows is set. The save event DA refresh the grid after save if needed.',
'The other DAs handle the poor man''s combo box.',
'See page attribute Function and Global Variables for adding to the selection action menu',
'and calling model.fetchAll.',
'<br>Issues:<br>',
'- It should be possible in all cases to update a hidden column with ',
'Value Protected = No using model.setValue. But currently it is not.',
'The reason LIST works is that it is only updated via the model defaultValue column property.',
'This requires making columns such as SEQ not hidden, then hiding them in report settings and optionally ',
'setting the advanced column configuration property features.canHide to false. The down',
'side is that the column shows up in the Columns dialog. Setting the Alternative Label can help.<br>',
'- After a refresh the IG Edit button does not reflect the correct edit state.<br>',
'- After an insert row the IG Edit button does not reflect the correct edit state.<br>',
'- Would be nice if Alt-Up/Down keys could be shortcuts for move up/down actions but the ',
'grid widget event handling gets in the way.<br>',
'- This would be a great use for a checkbox column item type; if there was one.<br>',
'- Would be nice if Show Completed could be done with client side filtering.<br>',
'- Would be nice if someday didn''t need the workaround for no data found error and',
'inserted row shows value rather than display value.<br>',
'- A quick way to delete a list is an exercise for the reader.<br>',
'</p>',
''))
,p_plug_query_options=>'DERIVED_REPORT_COLUMNS'
,p_attribute_01=>'N'
,p_attribute_02=>'HTML'
);
