,p_plug_display_point=>'BODY'
,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>A number of people have wanted a <a href=''https://community.oracle.com/message/14161863'' target=''_blank''>checkbox column</a> in IG.',
'The right thing to do is create a simple checkbox plugin that works with IG. But while we are waiting...',
'</p>',
'<p>It need not be an actual input checkbox element but should look like a checkbox.',
'Some people want it just for display and some for display and edit. This sample',
'is just for reporting not editing.',
'</p>',
'<p>The technique used here relies on the new apex.item function displayValueFor.',
'With a non-editable grid column items are still generated but they are essentially ',
'hidden item types; input type=hidden (no mater what the column Type is). ',
'Because there is no apex.item initialization for hidden inputs you can supply your own. ',
'This needs to be done before the IG is initialized so use Function and Global Variable Declaration.',
'The custom displayValueFor function returns icon markup for either a checked or',
'unchecked icon depending on the value it is given.',
'<p>Another clever idea for displaying a checkbox can be found <a href=''https://svenweller.wordpress.com/2017/03/29/apex-5-yn-icons/'' target=''_blank''>here</a>.',
'This uses a font icon class name formed by incorporating the value of the column.',
'</p>',
'<p>Demonstrates:<br>',
'Creating an apex.item instance and using the displayValueFor callback.</br>',
'<br>Customizations:<br>',
'The ONLEAVE column: give it a static id, align center, advanced config is used to keep it from stretching,',
'type is display only and don''t escape special characters.<br>',
'See page attribute Function and Global Variable Declaration for the apex.item.',
'<br>Issues:<br>',
'This example isn''t screen reader accessible (doesn''t say yes/no or checked/unchecked)',
'but that should be easily solved a few ways.',
'</p>'))
,p_plug_query_options=>'DERIVED_REPORT_COLUMNS'
,p_attribute_01=>'N'
,p_attribute_02=>'HTML'
);
