,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>This page demonstrates the advantage of having a separate model and view layer.',
'The IG grid view and Details form field are different views of data from the ',
'same model. When the selection changes the details region form fields are updated',
'with model data from the selected rows. Changes to form fields are set in the model.',
'Model notifications are used to keep the two views in sync. Server side processing',
'is exactly the same as if there were just the IG on the page.',
'</p>',
'<p>This provides the benefits of an IG for filtering, sorting etc. and ',
'the benefits of a form with custom layout and extra room for large fields like notes',
'and without having to popup a dialog. Specific logic is added to support ',
'multi-editing where values entered are set in all the selected rows.',
'</p>',
'<p>This also demonstrates the use of splitters. This is accomplished with custom',
'page template Fit to Window and region template Splitter.',
'Splitter regions must have exactly two sub regions. Regions that should resize',
'need to have the CSS class "resize".',
'Typically there is one top level region that is a splitter or one resizeable region.',
'Regions that need to resize have class "resize" in CSS Classes.',
'For regions probably want to change template options: Remove Body Padding, Bottom Margin: None.',
'IG must have Heading: Fixed to Region. The height will adjust as the window/splitters change.',
'<p>Customizations:<br>',
'Most of the work is done in 5 dynamic actions.',
'See Page attribute CSS: Inline for notes pop over and multi-edit styles. ',
'See Page attribute Function and Global Variable Declaration for model listener.',
'See IG attribute Advanced JavaScript Config for toolbar and action customizations.',
'<br>Issues:<br>',
'- To make this work I used private methods so this code is likely to break and need changes in the future.',
'Ideally in the future there will be public methods to support this kind of thing.<br>',
'- Editing a value in the form that isn''t a visible column will show in the wrong ',
'column in the grid. This is the edit hidden columns problem that has been discussed on the ',
'<a href=''https://community.oracle.com/thread/4035826'' target=''_blank''>forums</a>. ',
'This is only a display problem the data will save correctly.',
'This is bug 26260818 which will hopfully be fixed in the next patch release.<br>',
'- The hire Date is not always updated correctly because of issue with how date picker manages focus.</br>',
'- There are a number of issues or improvements that could be made to Fit to Window',
'and Splitter templates.<br>',
'</p>',
''))
,p_plug_query_options=>'DERIVED_REPORT_COLUMNS'
,p_attribute_01=>'N'
